{"title":"Review: The MET Rivale is a light, well-ventilated, reasonably priced road helmet","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/28/review-the-met-rivale-is-a-reasonably-priced-lightweight-well-ventilated-road-helmet/","date":1622206811000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>The MET Rivale is their mid-range road helmet, nestled between the Vinci MIPS and the ultra-ventilated Trenta helmets, priced at 130€. It actually shares the shape of their top-end aero road helmet, the Manta MIPS. This one is more of an all-rounder, though, with significantly more ventilation. We got this lightweight, reasonably priced road helmet in to check out the fit, comfort and coverage.</p><p><em>Feature Image by Finlay Anderson</em></p><figure id=\"attachment_260170\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260170\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb13/ng:webp/ngcb13\" alt=\"met rivale\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb13/ng:webp/ngcb13\" ezoid=\"0.13232374158300786\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083627/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helmet-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb13 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260170\">The ventilation on the MET Rivale is very good at speed. Photo by Finlay Anderson.</figcaption></figure><p>First up, the MET Rivale we tested does not include a MIPS liner. The Italian brand do offer the MET Rivale MIPS helmet for just 20€ more at 150€. We would always, always, recommend that riders chose a MIPS option over a helmet lacking in any rotational impact protection. Why? They are just safer (by around 10%)! If your budget can stretch to a helmet that offers protection against rotation-induced concussion injuries, then get one.</p><figure id=\"attachment_260172\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260172\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale road helmet sunglasses storage vents\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083640/Met-rivale-road-helemt-review-sunglasses-mount-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260172\">You can store your sunglasses in the vents of the MET Rivale, either right-way-up or upside down. Photo by Finlay Anderson.</figcaption></figure><p>Anyway, back to the MET Rivale we have on test. I got the small recommended for head circumferences of 52cm to 56cm. I sit smack bang in the middle of that range at 54cm. My Park Tool scales weighed it at 212g; that’s a bonus 8g lighter than the 220g claimed weight, for the weight weenies who care.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p>Arguably the most important feature of any helmet is the fit, and so this is what much of this review will focus on. While the fit and adjustability of this helmet is very good (not quite excellent), the comfort levels unfortunately came nowhere near those provided by the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/20/review-the-met-manta-mips-road-helmet-cuts-a-fine-aerodynamic-figure/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MET Manta MIPS</a> we tested recently. More on that later…</p><figure id=\"attachment_260179\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260179\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale retention system adjustable\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27084635/met-rivale-road-helmet-comfort-liner-retention-system-adjustable-vertically-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260179\">Photo by Finlay Anderson</figcaption></figure><p>The MET Rivale gets a 360° head belt tightened at the rear by a ponytail-compatible retention system. The vertical placement of that retention system can be adjusted to sit in one of three positions. While the availability of such an adjustment is welcome, I personally struggled to find a position that was 100% comfortable. In each of the three positions, upon tightening the retention system at the rear, I noticed significant pressure points above each ear.&nbsp;</p><figure id=\"attachment_260171\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260171\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale road helmet coverage\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083634/met-rivale-road-helemt-review-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260171\">Photo by Finlay Anderson</figcaption></figure><p>I also noticed a pressure point at the front of my head, slightly offset from center. Assuming I don’t have <em>too</em> asymmetrical a head (no comments, please), I removed the comfort liner in that region to look for any inconsistencies underneath.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale comfort liner\" width=\"1200\" 