t=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27101728/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-comfort-liner-velcro-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>Notice that the oval-shaped velcro tabs sit within dedicated recessed portions of the EPS. Some of the velcro tabs don’t sit perfectly within their recessed housing, resulting in a slightly uneven surface for the comfort liner to sit on. This, I think is the reason for the pressure point at the front of my head. This is an issue you’d be unlikely to encounter on the MET Rivale MIPS as the comfort liner sticks directly to the MIPS liner which is always going to be perfectly flat.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-4\"></span></p><figure id=\"attachment_259394\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-259394\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap.jpg\" alt=\"met manta mips road helmet review\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/20110347/met-manta-mips-road-helmet-fidlock-buckle-chin-strap-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-259394\">For me, the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/20/review-the-met-manta-mips-road-helmet-cuts-a-fine-aerodynamic-figure/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MET Manta MIPS</a> offered much better comfort over the MET Rivale. Photo by Finlay Anderson.</figcaption></figure><p>In contrast, over tightening the MET Manta MIPS retention system highlighted no particular pressure points, resulting in a really comfortable fit. The more expensive, more aerodynamic road helmet would certainly be my preference. Especially, as I live in the UK where it rarely gets very warm so ventilation isn’t super high on the list of priorities.</p><figure id=\"attachment_260177\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260177\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale road helmet vents\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083709/met-rivale-vents-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260177\">Photo by Finlay Anderson.</figcaption></figure><p>That said, the ventilation offered by the MET Rivale is good. There are ten elongated vents at the front of the helmet with another smaller one placed at the highest point. This one opens up into a cavity underneath the helmet, allowing air to flow over the top of the skull, pulling hot air out of two rear-facing vents.</p><figure id=\"attachment_260178\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260178\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083714/Met-road-helmet-rivale.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerum