0x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083714/Met-road-helmet-rivale-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083714/Met-road-helmet-rivale-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083714/Met-road-helmet-rivale-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083714/Met-road-helmet-rivale-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083714/Met-road-helmet-rivale-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260178\">Photo by Finlay Anderson</figcaption></figure><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-4\"></span>There are of course seven rear facing vents in total but only two of these have a direct inlet from which air flows through the body of the helmet.</p><figure id=\"attachment_260174\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260174\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale road helmet retention system\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083651/met-rivale-road-helmet-retention-inside-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260174\">Photo by Finlay Anderson</figcaption></figure><p>The MET Rivale retention system isn’t quite as adjustable as the one seen on the Manta MIPS. While the aero road helmet allows riders to move the cups further apart or closer to one another, the cups on the MET Rivale sit in a fixed position. That said, they do feature rubberized panels that should provide extra comfort for riders with little to no hair.</p><figure id=\"attachment_260196\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260196\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale road helmet\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27103452/met-rivale-review-road-cycling-helemt-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260196\">Photo by Finlay Anderson</figcaption></figure><p>Finally, we get to the chin strap. This is adjustable in just about every way. You can alter the overall length, as well as perfect the length of the straps that sit in front of and behind your ear; a very important feature in any helmet. The straps fasten with a standard plastic buckle.</p><h3>Can we recommend the MET Rivale?</h3><figure id=\"attachment_260175\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260175\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale road helmet pan shot\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/27083657/met-rivale-road-helmet-review-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260175\">Photo by Finlay Anderson</figcaption></figure><p>Yes, but not without reservation. While it is a lightweight, well-ventilated helmet offering reasonable coverage for the grams, it certainly isn’t the most comfortable road helmet we’ve tested. The more expensive MET Manta MIPS beats it hands down in that department. However, if you’re not looking for an aero road helmet, we’d recommend the Rivale MIPS next. It’s safer, cheaper, and the presence of the MIPS liner likely negates some of the issues with comfort we experienced with the non-MIPS counterpart tested here.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>Both MET Rivale helmets are available in sizes S (52-56cm), M (56-58cm) and L (58-61cm). They are CE certified according to AS/NZS and US standards.</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts.jpg\" alt=\"met rivale helemt mips 6 colorways\" width=\"1200\" height=\"621\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-297x154.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-800x414.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-120x62.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-768x397.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-696x360.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-1068x553.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-812x420.jpg 812w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-297x154.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-800x414.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-120x62.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-768x397.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-696x360.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-1068x553.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/met-rivale-and-met-rivale-mips-road-helemts-812x420.jpg 812w\"></a></p><p>The MET Rivale is priced at 130€ / £120 / CAD$200. The MET Rivale MIPS weighs just 20g more at 250g in medium, and will set you back 150€ / £140 / US$180 / CAD$250 / AUS$250. Availability is expected around mid-October.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-leader-1\"></span></p><p>There is no official distributor for MET Helmets in the US at this time. But, stay tuned, they will have some exiting news for US customers soon.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.met-helmets.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>MET-Helmets.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"1a1c356600abd5c1944f9eb392b03659781fabea5b0f4a113c7dd8d2da026f11","category":"Cycling"}